rcial drafting baseline — compliance/non-infringement","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/ucc"}],"title":"Compliance-with-laws / non-infringement warranty missing"},{"description":"No SLA / service level agreement / uptime commitment was found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"An MSA for hosted services without an SLA leaves availability promises unenforceable.","id":"MSA-016-s1-0","recommendation":"Reference an SLA (attached or linked) with uptime, support response, and remedy schedules.","rule_id":"MSA-016","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"msa-deep-commercial-drafting-baseline-sla-reference","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Commercial drafting baseline — SLA reference","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/ucc"}],"title":"SLA reference missing"},{"description":"The survival clause exists but does not name: IP ownership / assignment, indemnification.","document_position":1808,"excerpt":{"end_offset":2174,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":1808,"text":"5. Confidentiality. Each party (as \"Receiving Party\") shall hold in strict confidence all non-public information of the other party (as \"Disclosing Party\") designated as confidential or that reasonably should be understood to be confidential given the nature of the information. T"},"explanation":"Survival language is what keeps sticky obligations alive after a contract terminates. A survival clause that doesn't expressly enumerate the present-in-document confidentiality / IP / indemnity obligations creates ambiguity at the moment those obligations matter most — post-termination, when the contract has already ended.","id":"TEMP-012-s1-1808","recommendation":"Add explicit named references to the missing obligation(s): IP ownership / assignment, indemnification. Standard drafting names every sticky section by number or category in the survival clause.","rule_id":"TEMP-012","rule_version":"1.1.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"Survival clause does not name 2 sticky obligations"},{"description":"The contract references data but does not separately allocate data ownership.","document_position":4288,"excerpt":{"end_offset":4301,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":4288,"text":"10. Data Return. Upon termination, Vendor shall return all Customer data in a machine-readable format within thirty (30) days and delete all copies thereafter."},"explanation":"IP and data ownership are different. For SaaS, the customer typically owns its data; the vendor typically owns usage analytics. Address each explicitly.","id":"IPDATA-004-s1-4288","rule_id":"IPDATA-004","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Data ownership not separately addressed"},{"description":"No indemnification covering breach of confidentiality was found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Confidentiality breaches often produce damages that are difficult to quantify; indemnification anchors the remedy.","id":"MSA-003-s1-0","recommendation":"Add an indemnity for damages arising from breach of confidentiality obligations.","rule_id":"MSA-003","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"msa-deep-commercial-drafting-baseline-confidentiality-indemnity","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Commercial drafting baseline — confidentiality indemnity","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/ucc"}],"title":"Confidentiality breach indemnity missing"},{"description":"Indemnification appears to be excluded from the aggregate liability cap.","document_position":3469,"excerpt":{"end_offset":3535,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":3469,"text":"8. Limitation of Liability. (a) Aggregate Liability Cap. EACH PARTY'S AGGREGATE LIABILITY SHALL NOT EXCEED THE TOTAL FEES PAID BY CUSTOMER IN THE TWELVE (12) MONTHS IMMEDIATELY PRECEDING THE CLAIM. (b) Carveouts. The aggregate liability cap shall not apply to: (i) breach of confi"},"explanation":"Whether indemnification falls inside or outside the cap is the most contested cap-carve-out term. The report surfaces it for explicit review.","id":"MSA-005-s1-3469","recommendation":"Confirm intent: keep indemnity inside the cap (lower vendor exposure), put it outside (higher customer protection), or place it under a supercap (compromise).","rule_id":"MSA-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"msa-deep-commercial-drafting-baseline-indemnity-cap-interaction","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Commercial drafting baseline — indemnity / cap interaction","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/ucc"}],"title":"Indemnification excluded from liability cap"},{"description":"No termination-on-insolvency clause was found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"11 U.S.C. § 365 makes pure ipso-facto clauses unenforceable in some scenarios, but the contract should still anchor the parties' intent.","id":"MSA-019-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: termination on filing for bankruptcy, appointment of receiver, or assignment for the benefit of creditors.","rule_id":"MSA-019","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"msa-deep-11-u-s-c-365-bankruptcy-considerations","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"11 U.S.C. § 365 — Bankruptcy considerations","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/11/365"}],"title":"Termination for bankruptcy / insolvency missing"},{"description":"No transition / wind-down / hosted-service continuation period was found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Without a wind-down, the customer can be cut off mid-migration.","id":"MSA-020-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: vendor will continue providing the service for up to N (e.g., 90) days post-termination at then-current rates to facilitate transition.","rule_id":"MSA-020","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"msa-deep-commercial-drafting-baseline-transition-assistance","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Commercial drafting baseline — transition assistance","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/ucc"}],"title":"Wind-down / transition assistance missing"},{"description":"No bilateral force-majeure language was found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"A one-sided force-majeure clause (vendor-only) is commercially abnormal; payment obligations are conventionally excluded.","id":"MSA-022-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'neither party shall be liable for delay or failure due to force majeure', with a payment-obligation carve-out.","rule_id":"MSA-022","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"msa-deep-commercial-drafting-baseline-balanced-force-majeure","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Commercial drafting baseline — balanced force majeure","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/ucc"}],"title":"Balanced force majeure missing"},{"description":"No amendment-in-writing or no-waiver boilerplate found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Without these, oral modifications and unintentional waivers become litigation risks.","id":"MSA-025-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'no amendment is effective unless in writing signed by both parties' and 'no failure to enforce shall be deemed a waiver.'","rule_id":"MSA-025","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"msa-deep-commercial-drafting-baseline-amendment-waiver","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Commercial drafting baseline — amendment / waiver","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/ucc"}],"title":"Amendment-in-writing / no-waiver missing"},{"description":"No clause was found addressing AI / generative AI usage by the vendor in service delivery.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Increasingly the contract should disclose AI use, training data, and IP ownership of outputs (see the §49 AI Addendum playbook for the deep check).","id":"MSA-028-s1-0","recommendation":"Add a clause disclosing whether AI is used, naming material AI subprocessors, and addressing IP in outputs.","rule_id":"MSA-028","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"msa-deep-nist-ai-rmf-transparency-baseline","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"NIST AI RMF — transparency baseline","source_url":"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework"}],"title":"AI usage clause missing"},{"description":"Exclusive / limited remedy language is present but no UCC § 2-719(2) fail-of-essential-purpose escape was found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"UCC § 2-719(2) preserves alternative remedies when a limited remedy fails of its essential purpose — anchoring this protects the customer from a remedy gap.","id":"MSA-030-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'if the limited remedy is found to fail of its essential purpose, the customer's other remedies under this Agreement and applicable law remain available.'","rule_id":"MSA-030","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"msa-deep-u-c-c-2-719-2-","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"U.C.C. § 2-719(2)","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/ucc/2/2-719"}],"title":"UCC § 2-719 limited-remedy escape missing"},{"description":"EACH PARTY'S AGGREGATE LIABILITY SHALL NOT EXCEED THE TOTAL FEES PAID BY CUSTOMER IN THE TWELVE (12) MONTHS IMMEDIATELY  | The aggregate liability cap shall not apply to: (i) breach of confidentiality; (ii) indemnification obligations; or (iii","document_position":3288,"excerpt":{"end_offset":3429,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":3288,"text":"EACH PARTY'S AGGREGATE LIABILITY SHALL NOT EXCEED THE TOTAL FEES PAID BY CUSTOMER IN THE TWELVE (12) MONTHS IMMEDIATELY PRECEDING THE CLAIM."},"explanation":"Negative covenants restrict what a party may do. Surfacing them collectively makes it easier to check they are intended and consistent with the overall deal.","id":"OBLI-005-s1-3288","rule_id":"OBLI-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Negative covenants: 2"},{"description":"LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, EXEMPLARY, OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES","document_position":3704,"excerpt":{"end_offset":3785,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":3704,"text":"8. Limitation of Liability. (a) Aggregate Liability Cap. EACH PARTY'S AGGREGATE LIABILITY SHALL NOT EXCEED THE TOTAL FEES PAID BY CUSTOMER IN THE TWELVE (12) MONTHS IMMEDIATELY PRECEDING THE CLAIM. (b) Carveouts. The aggregate liability cap"},"explanation":"A waiver of consequential, special, incidental, and punitive damages is standard in commercial contracts. The waiver should be mutual unless deliberately asymmetric.","id":"RISK-007-s1-3704","rule_id":"RISK-007","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Consequential damages waiver present"},{"description":"Indemnity clause appears to be missing: defense control, settlement consent.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"7. Mutual Indemnification. (a) Vendor Indemnification. Vendor shall indemnify, defend, and hold harmless Customer from and against any third-party claim arising out of any allegation that the deliverables, as provided by Vendor and used in accordance with this Agreement, infringe"},"explanation":"A complete indemnity clause specifies (a) the timeline and form for notice of a claim, (b) which party controls defense, and (c) whether settlement requires consent.","id":"RISK-011-s1-0","rule_id":"RISK-011","rule_version":"1.3.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Indemnity procedural elements missing: defense control, settlement consent"},{"description":"confidentiality obligations shall survive termination for three (3) year","document_position":2100,"excerpt":{"end_offset":2172,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":2100,"text":"5. Confidentiality. Each party (as \"Receiving Party\") shall hold in strict confidence all non-public information of the other party (as \"Disclosing Party\") designated as confidential or that reasonably should be understood to be confidentia"},"explanation":"Typical post-termination confidentiality terms run 3–5 years for general information, with a perpetual duty for trade secrets. Verify the term matches the sensitivity of the information.","id":"RISK-014-s1-2100","rule_id":"RISK-014","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Confidentiality term length stated"},{"description":"The following defined terms are never used outside their definition: Customer Background IP.","document_position":1646,"excerpt":{"end_offset":1672,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":1646,"text":"Customer Background IP"},"explanation":"Defined terms that are not used downstream may be inherited from a template and obsolete. They clutter the contract and can confuse readers; either delete them or use them where intended.","id":"STRUCT-005-s1-1646","recommendation":"Review each unused term and either delete it or wire it into the relevant clause.","rule_id":"STRUCT-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Defined terms with no uses: 1"},{"description":"Provisions are stated to survive termination.","document_position":2134,"excerpt":{"end_offset":2153,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":2134,"text":"5. Confidentiality. Each party (as \"Receiving Party\") shall hold in strict confidence all non-public information of the other party (as \"Disclosing Party\") designated as confidential or that reasonably should be understood to be confidentia"},"explanation":"A survival clause names the obligations that outlast termination — typically confidentiality, indemnity, payment obligations accrued before termination, and choice of law.","id":"TEMP-006-s1-2134","rule_id":"TEMP-006","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Survival clause present"},{"description":"Survival clause does not appear to include: indemnity, payment, governing law.","document_position":2134,"excerpt":{"end_offset":2153,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":2134,"text":"5. Confidentiality. Each party (as \"Receiving Party\") shall hold in strict confidence all non-public information of the other party (as \"Disclosing Party\") designated as confidential or that reasonably should be understood to be confidentia"},"explanation":"Typical surviving obligations include confidentiality, indemnity, accrued payment obligations, and governing law. Missing any of these is common and worth confirming.","id":"TEMP-007-s1-2134","rule_id":"TEMP-007","rule_version":"1.2.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Survival list may be missing categories: indemnity, payment, governing law"},{"description":"Upon termination, Vendor shall return","document_position":4246,"excerpt":{"end_offset":4283,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":4246,"text":"10. Data Return. Upon termination, Vendor shall return all Customer data in a machine-readable format within thirty (30) days and delete all copies thereafter."},"explanation":"Post-termination obligations typically include return or destruction of confidential materials, deletion of data, and a certificate of destruction.","id":"TERM-007-s1-4246","rule_id":"TERM-007","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Post-termination obligations enumerated"}],"playbook_id":"msa-vendor-deep","playbook_match_confidence":1,"playbook_match_reasoning":"forced via sidecar to msa-vendor-deep","result_hash":"d62a96ae24cbaa12d2e20eeb9e19f3bb6c89bf3c2d6f4e06e540b0636a14431c","source_file":{"name":"msa-vendor-deep-missing-service-warranties-fail.txt","sha256":"f8e2e8cdeef28d5b073441ff40f754d90135a79d698280521e83dcce5f9b682d","size_bytes":1},"version":"9.41.0"}